17:07.666 --> 17:12.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
AVIK ROY: Thanks, Judy.

17:14.766 --> 17:19.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: One week
ago, Iraqi Prime Minister
Haider al-Abadi proclaimed
victory over ISIS

17:23.433 --> 17:25.466 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in Mosul.

17:25.466 --> 17:28.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But reality on the
ground is different, as
the fight continues in
parts of the Old City

17:28.966 --> 17:31.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
against ISIS holdouts.

17:31.000 --> 17:35.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As special correspondent
Marcia Biggs and videographer
Alessandro Pavone report, the

17:37.033 --> 17:39.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
human toll of the fighting
is becoming apparent.

17:39.533 --> 17:41.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And it is horrific.

17:41.566 --> 17:45.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A warning: Many viewers may
find images and accounts
in this story disturbing.

17:47.900 --> 17:51.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARCIA BIGGS: This is
what so-called liberated
Mosul looks and sounds
like, in a small pocket

18:01.433 --> 18:06.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of the Old City, the war
against ISIS seemingly ongoing.

18:06.066 --> 18:11.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And this is the Old City
from ground level, a scene
of utter devastation,
entire neighborhoods

18:14.700 --> 18:19.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
flattened by coalition
airstrikes, leaving
the few survivors to
search for the remains

18:20.433 --> 18:22.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of their loved ones.

18:22.466 --> 18:26.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Bashar and Ali's families were
together in this house hit
by an airstrike 28 days ago.

18:28.566 --> 18:31.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Ali names the dead one by one.

18:31.800 --> 18:36.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ALI, Mosul Resident (through
translator): My mother, three
brothers, three sisters,

18:38.033 --> 18:39.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
my father, two
sisters-in-law, two nieces.

18:39.833 --> 18:42.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: And you're the
only one left from your family.

18:42.633 --> 18:44.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ALI (through translator): Yes.

18:44.166 --> 18:46.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Shu Bedak Tamel,
what are you going to do now?

18:46.466 --> 18:48.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN (through translator):
What can I do?

18:48.900 --> 18:51.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I just want to take the
bodies out and bury them.

18:51.333 --> 18:56.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Mosul is the
capital of Nineveh Province and
it is the men of Nineveh's civil

18:58.233 --> 19:01.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
defense unit that are
responsible for pulling
the dead out of the rubble.

19:03.333 --> 19:06.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They arrive with their crude
tools, an ancient jackhammer,
a broken sledgehammer, and when

19:09.800 --> 19:14.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
all else fails, they
use their hands.

19:16.766 --> 19:20.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One of the family members is
adamant that the family is
under this spot in a washroom.

19:21.466 --> 19:25.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
"Just open the hole,"
this family member says.

19:25.533 --> 19:30.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But trying to drill through
over a foot of concrete proves
impossible and one of the

19:30.466 --> 19:33.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
relatives finds another
way into the house.

19:33.300 --> 19:36.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So we enter the
ruins in the dark.

19:36.000 --> 19:39.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So this was the washroom
they were talking about.

19:39.466 --> 19:44.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He's saying there's
a baby inside.

19:45.600 --> 19:48.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
In total, they are
looking for 18 bodies.

19:48.233 --> 19:51.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There were two families in the
adjoining houses that night.

19:51.633 --> 19:56.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Bashar lost six members of
his family, including his
wife and four children.

19:56.600 --> 20:01.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BASHAR, Mosul Resident (through
translator): We tried to
escape the day before, but ISIS

20:02.200 --> 20:03.700 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
shot at us.

20:03.700 --> 20:05.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We ran back to the house and
the army told us, stay inside.

20:05.933 --> 20:08.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We will evacuate you when
we make the area safe.

20:08.933 --> 20:11.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But the next morning, the
airstrike hit our house.

20:11.333 --> 20:13.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
There were two bombs.

20:13.033 --> 20:16.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
MARCIA BIGGS: Were you
in the house when the
explosion happened?

20:16.633 --> 20:20.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BASHAR (through translator):
Yes, but I was near the
front door of this house.

20:20.133 --> 20:23.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I was the only one who
didn't get injured, along
with my neighbor's family.

20:23.933 --> 20:26.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And my youngest daughter
was rescued by the army.

20:26.400 --> 20:28.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She's still alive.

20:28.333 --> 20:32.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: The
remnants of life that
night are frozen in time.

20:34.333 --> 20:38.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Food sits uneaten on
the kitchen counter, but
the clock still runs.

20:39.366 --> 20:40.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Hours pass, then
finally a breakthrough.

20:40.866 --> 20:42.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's a skull.

20:42.633 --> 20:46.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So they're telling me
they have no idea who
that little girl was.

20:46.200 --> 20:50.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There were six or seven little
girls in that room, and the
body is so decomposed, all there

20:50.933 --> 20:53.133 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
is, is a skull.

20:53.133 --> 20:58.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The search for remains
lasts all day, with
relatives waiting nervously.

20:59.266 --> 21:04.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
"God protect them,"
this one says.

21:05.566 --> 21:08.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They found four bodies
out of 18, 14 left to go.

21:08.666 --> 21:12.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The smell of death
is unbearable.

21:12.000 --> 21:16.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the members of Mosul's civil
defense, it's an ordinary day.

21:16.533 --> 21:19.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The day before, they pulled
19 bodies from the rubble.

21:19.800 --> 21:24.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Rabih Mishaal Mohamed is a
sergeant with the unit, all of
whom are working without pay.

21:27.100 --> 21:29.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RABIH MISHAAL MOHAMED,
Sergeant (through translator):
The hardest part is when
you see a child under

21:29.633 --> 21:32.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the rubble because he is
innocent, he is a child.

21:32.833 --> 21:35.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He has nothing to do with
the army or ISIS or anyone.

21:35.466 --> 21:37.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MARCIA BIGGS: Why
do you do this?

21:37.500 --> 21:40.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RABIH MISHAAL MOHAMED (through
translator): It is very
difficult for us, but they are

21:40.466 --> 21:44.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
like family, our brothers our
fathers, mothers, friends.

21:44.166 --> 21:47.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
If we don't take their bodies
out, who will come and do that?

21:47.033 --> 21:48.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So we withstand it.

21:48.200 --> 21:50.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We have to withstand it.

21:50.133 --> 21:53.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MARCIA BIGGS: Withstand
it, they must.

21:53.466 --> 21:58.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's a scene that will play
out again and again in the
days to come, a tiny sliver of

22:01.500 --> 22:06.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
comfort to the families,
who are clinging to what
little they can find.

22:08.433 --> 22:11.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour,"
I'm Marcia Biggs in the
Old City, West Mosul, Iraq.

22:18.700 --> 22:23.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: At the
White House, it is Made
in America Week, an effort
to highlight President

22:27.666 --> 22:32.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Trump's goal of boosting U.S.
manufacturing and job creation.

22:32.066 --> 22:37.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
However, it has again
sparked questions over
Mr. Trump and his family's
businesses, particularly

22:38.233 --> 22:40.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
where their products
are manufactured.

22:40.866 --> 22:42.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
John Yang has the story.

22:42.866 --> 22:47.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Today, the White
House South Lawn was turned into
a showcase for products made

22:48.000 --> 22:50.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in each of the 50 states.

22:50.033 --> 22:54.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But not on display, merchandise
sold by the Trump Organization
or Ivanka Trump's fashion

22:54.833 --> 22:56.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
