of products to five specific
countries, Bangladesh, China,

23:43.633 --> 23:47.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
India, Indonesia, and Vietnam.

23:47.066 --> 23:51.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's also customs records
that show that, back in 2013,
some of her shoes were made

23:51.766 --> 23:53.800 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in Ethiopia.

23:53.800 --> 23:58.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the brand told us that,
while they would like to bring
manufacturing back to the United

23:58.066 --> 24:02.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
States, they don't feel like
it's really possible to do
in a large-scale fashion.

24:02.166 --> 24:04.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: And how
does this compare?

24:04.066 --> 24:08.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We should also note that
the Trump brand, the Trump
Organization brand products made

24:08.733 --> 24:12.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in about 12 different countries,
including Bangladesh and China.

24:12.266 --> 24:15.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How does this compare with
the rest of the industry?

24:15.133 --> 24:20.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATEA GOLD: Well, the reality
is that the American apparel
industry is very firmly grounded

24:21.333 --> 24:23.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in globalization and
overseas production.

24:23.466 --> 24:28.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
About 97 percent of the clothes
and shoes sold here in the
United States are made abroad.

24:30.433 --> 24:34.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And industry experts say that
it is going to be incredibly
difficult to reverse that

24:34.266 --> 24:36.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
trend.

24:36.833 --> 24:40.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, the focus in the
industry right now is not
on bringing manufacturing
back in a large-scale

24:42.166 --> 24:45.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
fashion, but rather trying
to give consumers a sense of
confidence that their goods are

24:47.366 --> 24:49.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not being made by workers
overseas who are being
exploited for their labor.

24:49.733 --> 24:53.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: And how does
the Ivanka Trump fashion
line measure up to the
rest of the industry

24:53.933 --> 24:58.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and that sort of thing in
policing labor conditions
at the factories they use?

25:01.066 --> 25:04.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATEA GOLD: We found that the
Ivanka Trump brand lags behind
many in the apparel industry,

25:07.166 --> 25:10.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
both large and small
companies, when it comes
to having oversight of
their foreign production.

25:11.933 --> 25:15.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Up to now, they have really
relied on their suppliers to
certify that they are complying

25:17.400 --> 25:20.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with their code of conduct, a
code of conduct, I should note,
that they would not publicly

25:20.366 --> 25:22.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
disclose.

25:22.500 --> 25:26.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They are taking measures now
to do greater oversight, the
kind of measures that other

25:28.366 --> 25:32.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
companies already have,
such as bringing in a
group to independently
audit factories and

25:34.266 --> 25:37.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to provide some programs on the
ground to support some of the
women who make their clothes.

25:39.233 --> 25:42.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And what did the
Trump people say to you?

25:42.233 --> 25:45.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, Sean Spicer was asked
today about some of this in the
White House briefing, and said

25:45.366 --> 25:50.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it would be inappropriate for
him to talk about a private
business at the White House

25:50.366 --> 25:51.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
podium.

25:51.900 --> 25:53.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What did they tell you in
response to these things?

25:53.900 --> 25:57.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATEA GOLD: Well, the president
of the Ivanka Trump brand,
Abigail Klem, told us that one

25:57.933 --> 26:02.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the reasons they had not
taken these other measures that
other companies have is because

26:02.000 --> 26:07.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they're a newer and smaller
brand and that they're looking
now to really try to live

26:08.933 --> 26:12.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
their mission of women who
work, which is the motto Ivanka
Trump developed at her company

26:13.233 --> 26:15.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
throughout their
whole supply chain.

26:15.266 --> 26:19.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that is something that they
said is evolving and they're
going to continue to strive to

26:19.066 --> 26:21.200 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
do.

26:21.200 --> 26:24.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But Klem also told us that the
goal of bringing manufacturing
back to the United States for

26:24.033 --> 26:29.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
their company was just
unrealistic, that there
aren't trained workers
that work in the apparel

26:29.033 --> 26:33.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
industry here anymore, and,
in many cases, the machinery
doesn't even exist to do this

26:33.133 --> 26:35.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
kind of production.

26:35.233 --> 26:39.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Matea, let me ask you
about something else you have
been reporting on for The Post.

26:41.200 --> 26:44.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The financial -- the campaign
spending records of the Trump
2020 campaign shows that they

26:46.300 --> 26:49.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
paid money to -- they paid
fees to Donald Trump Jr.'s
lawyer before this latest story

26:51.833 --> 26:56.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
