been incurred all but for the
campaign committee, they can

28:11.266 --> 28:13.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
pay them.

28:13.333 --> 28:15.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But if they were expenses that
aren't related to political
activity, they're beyond the

28:15.533 --> 28:17.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
purview of the committee.

28:17.533 --> 28:21.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The fact that these payments
were made through the reelection
committee suggests that they

28:21.166 --> 28:26.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are connected to some sort of
legal investigation or legal
work connected to the campaign.

28:28.133 --> 28:30.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Matea Gold on legal
fees being paid for by the
campaign and Ivanka Trump's

28:30.433 --> 28:32.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
businesses, thank you very much.

28:32.933 --> 28:37.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MATEA GOLD: Thank you.

